  "prompt": "Is there a way to sort by the most upvoted answers on Quora?",
  "response": "On Quora, there isn't a direct feature that allows you to sort answers by the number of upvotes. Quora tends to display answers based on a combination of factors, such as relevance, quality, and engagement, which might include upvotes but isn't limited to them. This means the most upvoted answers might naturally appear higher in the list, but you can't sort strictly by upvotes.\n\nIf you're interested in finding highly upvoted answers, you might consider looking at the top answers of popular questions or checking out the profiles of prominent users. Additionally, sometimes third-party tools or browser extensions might offer ways to filter or view Quora content differently, but these aren't officially supported by Quora and should be used with caution.",
